{"question":"\r\n<div class='specification'>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">The following frequency distribution of marks has mean 4.5.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\"><br /><img src=\"./ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/408/bbc3.png\" alt=\"\" /></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;'>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">Find the value of <em>x</em>.</span></p>\r\n<div class='marks'>[4]</div>\r\n<div class='question_part_label'>a.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;'>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">Write down the standard deviation.</span></p>\r\n<div class='marks'>[2]</div>\r\n<div class='question_part_label'>b.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n","markschems":"\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px;'>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">\\(\\sum {fx = 1(2) + 2(4) +&nbsp; \\ldots&nbsp; + 7(4)} \\) , \\(\\sum {fx = 146 + 5x} \\)&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1&nbsp; </strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">evidence of substituting into mean \\(\\frac{{\\sum {fx} }}{{\\sum f }}\\)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong> </em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">correct equation&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1 </strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">e.g. \\(\\frac{{146 + 5x}}{{34 + x}} = 4.5\\) , \\(146 + 5x = 4.5(34 + x)\\)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">\\(x = 14\\)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; N2&nbsp; </strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">[4 marks]</span></strong></em></p>\r\n<div class='question_part_label'>a.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class='question' style='padding-left: 20px;'>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">\\(\\sigma = 1.54\\)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A2 &nbsp; &nbsp; N2</strong> </em></span></p>\r\n<p><em><strong><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;\">[2 marks]</span></strong></em></p>\r\n<div class='question_part_label'>b.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n","topic0":"Topic 5 - Statistics and probability","topic1":"5.1","topic2":"Presentation of data: frequency distributions (tables); frequency histograms with equal class intervals","ReferenceCode":"10M.2.sl.TZ1.4"}